items.title: Hegseth reaffirms Vietnam partnership and hands over a leather box, belt and knife—wartime artifacts taken by U.S. soldiers
items.description: “Today we will exchange artifacts and information from the war with the goal of helping family members in both countries find peace.”

items.title: Trump says immigration raid efforts ‘haven’t gone far enough’
items.description: Trump said the tactics used by immigration agents were acceptable “because you have to get the people out.”

items.title: Stock futures climb as investors await Supreme Court showdown on Trump tariffs and shareholder vote on Musk’s $1 trillion pay package
items.description: On Thursday, Tesla shareholders will gather for the company's annual meeting and will vote on Musk's $1 trillion compensation package.

items.title: Fearing for her children’s safety, Mississippi woman shoots and kills escaped research monkey
items.description: “I shot at it and it just stood there, and I shot again, and he backed up and that's when he fell.”

items.title: Transportation secretary says he doesn’t plan to fire air traffic controllers who don’t show up for work during shutdown
items.description: Before the shutdown, the FAA was already dealing with a long-standing shortage of about 3,000 air traffic controllers.
